  "instructions": [
    "cook whole wheat spaghetti in boiling water until al dente.",
    "heat canola oil in a large skillet over medium heat.",
    "add small onion and cook until translucent.",
    "add dried austrian currants, lemon juice, ayurvedic ghee, salt, black pepper, turmeric, and ginger to the skillet and stir to combine.",
    "add cooked spaghetti to the skillet and toss to coat with the currant mixture.",
    "stir in fresh parsley, cilantro, and water to create a pasta-water-emulsion.",
    "serve immediately and garnish with additional fresh herbs if desired."
